# EmailJS Configuration
# Get these values from https://www.emailjs.com/
# 1. Create an account and service
# 2. Create an email template
# 3. Get your Public Key from the Account > API Keys section

NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_USER_ID=your_public_key_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxx

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual EmailJS credentials
# 3. The User ID should be your Public Key (not Private Key)
# 4. Make sure .env.local is in your .gitignore (it should be by default)

# Note: Never commit your actual .env.local file to git
# The private key is not needed for client-side EmailJS integration
